               <history>
                  <origin><p>unknown</p></origin>
                  <provenance><p>From Takamiya and Linenthal 2012, p. 184: <quote>Ambrosius, Opera, part 1 only (of
                     three), Basel, Johann Amerbach, 1492. A folio bound in seventeenth-century
                     calf, probably in Aberdeen, vellum manuscript fragment serving as a sewing
                     guard at the front of the volume. The manuscript dates from the first half of
                     the fourteenth century, and the fragment preserves a virtually complete column
                     of text (originally double columns), written in brown ink in twenty-one lines
                     of gothic script, ruled lightly with brown ink; the fragment measures 265 x
                     80mm and is in excellent condition. The Middle English glosses are written
                     between the lines in red ink. The text comes from the sections on trees (recto)
                     and birds (verso) and corresponds to lines 677-704 and 762-82 of the 1990
                     edition.</quote> Now owned by Toshiyoki Takamiya.</p></provenance>
               </history>
